<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum21/HTML/002276.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cherrie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I was wondering which is actually better dual wielding two weapons or using a two hander? been bothering me thanks =)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sinda Ashenheart</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I think this will come down to a personal (and situational) preferance response. I personally keep both skills maxed. Normally I used to prefer 1HS and dual wield except when fighting things with damage shields, at which time I'd switch to 2HS. But I recently got a Lang of the Wolves and have pretty much put away my regular Lang's except for the time when I hit a new level and want to max out my 1HS again. But sometimes it's nice to slice and dice non-stop.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"><P>My problem is attempting to get bash up. Well, that and piercing. Bah.<P>Sinda Ashenheart<BR>Love and Honor Guild of Veeshan</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Barudin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Here is my answer to this....<P>First off when I am the primary tank and my job is to simply taunt the attacker while the rest of the group kills it....duel wielding is the way to go....You appear to taunt better cuz mobs seem to like not getting hit that often.  My recommendation for weapons would be low levels (duel langseaxs) mid levels to upper levels (duel SSOY's or duel EBW's).<P><BR>Now if you are not the primary tank...ie there are others in the group and you are not the one tanking to mob the most....I love using the mith 2hander and Thick Banded Belt Combination....Its a real fast combo and you do massive amounts of damage...I have not had the please of planes weapons yet but I will some day.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">segorn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR>  The answer to this one is ... it depends.<P>  At mid levels, you are usually going to do more damage with a big 2 hander than dual weild. Conversely you will generally taunt better with dual weild.<P>  At high levels, you'll want to switch to duael weild. Due to the way verant's combat algorythm works, dual weilding low delay weapons will outdamage a 2 hander against anything except a green or low blue. This is true even though a raw damage/delay comparison doesn't show it.<P>  The reason is that at high levels, your modal (not max, modal e.g. most common) weapon damage is :<P>  2 X DMG + (lvl-25)/3<P>  Not that the additive component (lvl-25)/3 which is not a function of DMG. This skews everything in favor of a low delay weapon.<P>  Example:<P>  I can hit 2 times with an exe axe or 6 times with my yaks (this is a little unfair to the yaks; more like 6.5 hits per 100 time units is reasonable).<P>  Exe axe modal damage : 2 X 25 + 8 = 58<P>  Two swings so total damage : 116<P>  Yak modal damage : 2 X 8 + 8 = 24<P>  Six swings so total damage : 144<P>  This discounts the weapon procs, etc.<P>  The fact is that at high levels dual weild outdamages and outtaunts a 2 hander, even if the raw damage/delay numbers don't seem to support such an assertion. <BR>  I actually think this was something that Verant never realize when they cooked up their combat damage rules, but its probably too late to change it now.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Malariskis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">This is really not an answer, but do any warriors find it feasible to use a shield and a 1 handed slashing?<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Milena</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">quote:</font><HR>This is really not an answer, but do any warriors find it feasible to use a shield and a 1 handed slashing?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Only if the spells the creature is casting are so damaging to the group, be it through damage caused, charms, or healing, that reducing your damage output is worth it to interrupt the spells.<P>I found that switching to my shield in order to bash the very annoying lizardman healer types was worth it.<P>Milena<BR>40 warrior on prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kelthanor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Another thing to keep in mind is that the big 2-handers will do <B>much</B> higher damage on a successful riposte than a fast 1-hander.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Bartho</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">In my experience it all comes down to what you have available in each catagory. A while back I tested Mithril 2H+TBB vs. 2Ykesha+SSB I found them to be roughly equal for me, so I pretty much wielded whatever I felt like depending on my mood at the time  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>Then not too long ago I managed to get my hands on a Razing Sword of Skarlon, I haven't used the Ykesha's since (but I do keep them around cause they are currently my best dual-wield combo and I like to have the option to effectively dual wield open).<P>I guess what I'm getting at is ... 2H is currently the best option for me due to what I have available. Look at the options you have and maybe even do a little testing, and choose what you feel is the optimum setup for you, nobody else can really give you a straight answer on something like that, you have to figure out what would be best for you (and though 2H is currently better for me, when I manage to get my hands on spined dragon claws + bloodfire that's probably going to change ... until I get an Ashenbone Warhammer, etc ...  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"> )<P>Bartho</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kailyn of Povar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">At the moment at the highest levels 1h seems to have an advantage. THere seem to be 2 factors contributing to this. One is the the frequncy that hits for the Magic Number come up with. On low damage weapons the MN is reletivly closer to max damage so that each of these hits is more efficient. Also there are fewer hit above the MN than below it. the second effect that adds to the effectiveness of 1h weapons, especially, fast weapons (which often have lower damage) is the minimum hit you get with the primary hand. Scoring a lot of minimum hits of 8 with a Ykesha is a lot more efficent than socring a lot of 9 with a Mith 2 Hander.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
